Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of seven (7) years.   Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by five (5) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Pay costs of action; 
2) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge; 
3) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
4) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety, no possession nor consume alcohol or illegal drugs;
6) The court authorizes the Department of Corrections to withhold funds from any inmate account belonging to the defendant;
7) No contact with K.S., DOB: 08-01-2000 without agent approval; 
8) No contact with any person under the age of 18 without prior agent approval except incidental contact; 
9) Have no jobs with anyone under the age of 18 without agent approval; 
10)Comply with sex offender registry for the period of supervision followed by 15 years after discharge; 
11) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
12) Defendant is subject to GPS monitoring if the department feels it is necessary; 
13) No internet access or use of social media without prior agent approval.
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is given 47 days sentence credit.  
Minutes.
